---
By: Lao-tzu
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 358
    Verse: 18
Tags:
  - Perfection
---
The perfect man employs his mind as a mirror. It grasps nothing： It refuses
nothing. It receives, but doesn’t keep. Thus he can triumph over matter,
without injury to himself.
